===Noun===
'''paradiddle'''
# {{music}} A [[percussive]] [[exercise]] (one of 26 [[drum]] [[rudiments]]) which involves playing one [[hit]] with the leading hand, the next with the other, followed by two hits with the leading hand, usually followed by a second paradiddle using the other hand to lead. Thus, if R represents the right hand and L represents the left hand, a paradiddle led by the right hand would be played RLRR. A continuous roll of paradiddles would usually be RLRRLRLL...